ENTRY            33219   20251209   20260508   20260508       3222
SUBENT        33219001   20251209   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                 12         28
TITLE      Independent isomeric yield ratios of fission products
            in the epi-cadmium neutron induced fission of 238Pu
AUTHOR     (H.Naik, R.J.Singh, S.P.Dange, W.Jang)
INSTITUTE  (3INDTRM,3KORKNU)
REFERENCE  (J,RPC,217,111505,2024)
FACILITY   (REAC,3INDTRM) APSARA reactor
SAMPLE     For short-lived fission products, 100 uL of nitrate
            solutions of 238Pu (50 ug/ml) were sealed in three
            different polypropylene tubes of about 2 cm long and
            3-mm inner diameter.
           For long-lived fission products, an electrodeposited
            target of 238Pu (~20 ug) was covered with
            0.075-mm-thick Lexan catcher foils, sealed with
            alkathene bags.
            The individual targets were wrapped with 1-mm-thick
            cadmium foil.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) 120 cm3 detector (1.8 keV energy resolution
            for 1332.5 keV gamma-line of 60Co.)
METHOD     Off-line gamma-ray spectrometry: for short-lived
            fission products targets were irradiated for 10-11 min
            at a flux of 1.2 X 10**12 n/cm2/sec, while for
            long-lived fission products targets were irradiated
             for 55-60 min.
MISC-COL   (MISC) fission fragment angular momenta Jrms
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
STATUS     (APRVD) Proof-read by H.Naik (2025-12-14)
           (TABLE,,H.Naik+,J,RPC,217,111505,2024) Table 2
HISTORY    (20251209C) VT
ENDBIB              28
COMMON               1          3
EN-MIN
EV
        0.5
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           35
